            "library": "H5P.MultiChoice 1.16",
            "params": {
              "question": "<p>A fracture at the pterion is clinically dangerous because it can rupture which vessel?</p>",
              "answers": [
                {
                  "text": "<div>Superficial temporal artery</div>",
                  "correct": false,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>The superficial temporal artery runs superficially in the temporal region and is not endangered by a pterion fracture.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                },
                {
                  "text": "<div>Anterior branch of the middle meningeal artery</div>",
                  "correct": true,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>Correct. The pterion is the thinnest part of the skull and directly overlies this artery. Rupture leads to extradural haematoma, a neurosurgical emergency.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                },
                {
                  "text": "<div>Maxillary artery</div>",
                  "correct": false,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>The maxillary artery lies deep within the infratemporal fossa and is not directly at risk from a pterion fracture.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                },
                {
                  "text": "<div>Middle cerebral artery</div>",
                  "correct": false,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>The middle cerebral artery is an intracranial vessel lying beneath the dura. It is not the artery torn in a pterion fracture.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                }
              ],
              "overallFeedback": [
                {
                  "from": 0,
                  "to": 50,
                  "feedback": "The pterion overlies the anterior branch of the middle meningeal artery. A fracture at this thinnest point of the skull tears this artery, causing extradural haematoma — one of the most important neurosurgical emergencies in head injury."
                },
                {
                  "from": 51,
                  "to": 100,
                  "feedback": "Correct! The pterion overlies the anterior branch of the middle meningeal artery. A fracture here tears this artery, causing bleeding between the dura and the skull — an extradural haematoma requiring emergency surgical evacuation."
                }
              ],
